The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump declaring March 2020 as American Red Cross Month. The American Red Cross is a humanitarian organization that provides support and assistance during emergencies and disasters, both in the United States and internationally. The proclamation recognizes the dedication of the organization's volunteers, employees, and supporters who provide shelter, care, and compassion to those in need. It also highlights the American Red Cross's role in providing blood products, teaching life-saving skills, supporting the military and veterans, and providing international humanitarian aid. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of observing American Red Cross Month and supporting the work of the organization.